=== Helper Function ===
auth_user_exists_v1(p_email text):
- SECURITY DEFINER, search_path = public
- Reads from auth.users only
- Returns boolean -- true if email exists, false if not
- Case-insensitive match via lower()
- REVOKE ALL FROM PUBLIC -- service_role access only (implicit, no explicit grant)
- Excluded from rpc-mapping-contract gate (internal helper, not public RPC)

=== Edge Function Revised Logic ===
New user (not in auth.users):
  calls supabase.auth.admin.inviteUserByEmail(email, { redirectTo: APP_URL/auth })
Existing user (in auth.users):
  calls supabase.auth.signInWithOtp({ email, options: { shouldCreateUser: false, emailRedirectTo: APP_URL/auth } })
Both paths:
  user lands on /auth
  /post-auth calls accept_pending_invites_v1()
  invite resolved automatically
Email failure: non-blocking -- invite row always created

=== Guards ===
APP_URL guard: returns 'misconfigured' if env not set
shouldCreateUser: false -- prevents accidental user creation
email normalized: trim().toLowerCase()

=== Magic Link Template Dependency ===
Supabase Magic Link email template repurposed for existing-user re-invite emails
Subject: You've been invited to join Wholesale Hub
